# GladME Studio: Evolution from V2/V3 to V4
# Technical Improvement Report & Architectural Comparison

[ABSTRACT]
This report details the comprehensive transition of the GladME Studio Agentic IDE from its version 2/3 prototypes to the production-ready version 4.0.0.

[BACKEND ARCHITECTURE]
- API Framework: FastAPI (Modularized)
- State Persistence: SQLAlchemy ORM
- Configuration: Centralized .env
- Execution: Docker Containerized Sandbox
- LLM Access: Multi-Provider Router

[FRONTEND DESIGN]
- Monaco Editor Integration
- Visual Workflow (React Flow)
- Persistence: Chat & Logs
- Theming: Unified Dark Mode

[SECURITY]
- JWT Authentication
- RBAC (Role-Based Access Control)
- Secure Token Storage

[SANDBOXING]
- Docker-based isolation (gladme-runner:latest)
- Host system protection

[AI ROUTING]
- Fallback Chain: Ollama -> OpenAI -> Anthropic

[ECOSYSTEM]
- Skills System (security-scan, generate-docs)
- MCP Server/Client Support

[ROADMAP]
- Streaming AI
- Collaborative Editing
- Native Desktop Wrapper
- CI/CD Integration
